{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Lightly grease the Varoma dish and tray and set aside. Place Kaffir lime leaves into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>10 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add beans and spring onions\/shallots and chop <nobr>6-8 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Transfer into a large bowl and set aside.","Place fish pieces, curry paste, coconut cream and egg white into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>Turbo\/1 sec\/3 times<\/nobr>, or until mix is well combined but not puréed.","Add fish mixture to reserved bean mixture and fold through to combine. Roll mix into 18 equal-sized balls (approx. 1 heaped tablespoon each) then, using slightly damp hands, gently flatten each ball to form fish cakes. Place each fish cake into the greased Varoma dish and tray, being careful not to let the fish cakes touch. If necessary, steam your fish cakes in batches.","Place water into mixing bowl and place Varoma into position. Steam <nobr>15 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. If cooking in batches, check water level between each batch. The water level should never drop below 500 g.","Serve fish cakes warm garnished with beanshoots, chilli and extra spring onions\/shallots."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["oil, for greasing","4 fresh Kaffir lime leaves, stalks removed","100 g fresh green beans, trimmed","2 spring onions\/shallots, trimmed, cut into pieces, plus extra for garnishing","600 g white fish fillets (e.g. snapper, perch), cut into pieces (3-4 cm)","100 g Red Thai Curry Paste","60 g canned coconut cream","1 egg white","800 g water","bean shoots, for garnishing","1 long red chilli, thinly sliced, for garnishing"]}],"id":"r68602","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-BbhzDha97to\/XZVPsdONxPI\/AAAAAAAAc7k\/r-HFvOHir10My0t-WCQM5F-9mt0r0js5gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_CoIoDLevZ30SuhXU.png","title":"Steamed Thai-style fish cakes","publishedAt":"2014-09-05T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"47 g","fat":"52 g","uom":"per 3 pieces","car